race.comment: Former Tony Gollan galloper SHE'S GOT LYRICS (1) hit the frame when having her first run for the new stable and will have come on with that run now under the belt. Drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley and should be right there when the judge calls a halt. RUN FREDA RUN (4) may have suffered from the dreaded second-up syndrome last time out but go on the good runner-up finish when resuming. Can bounce right back without surprising. RISE AND RESIST (2) strips fitter third-up from the spell and will find this easier than recent efforts. Look for a strong showing. CASH PIT (3) put in a career-best performance at the latest outing and can feature with a repeat of that effort. MAHTIKKAINSTINCT (5) rounds out the selections.
